    "body": "Problem:  ext_messages cannot tell when the screen or 'cmdheight' area\r\n          is cleared, which is needed to clear visible messages.\r\nSolution: Repurpose the \"msg_show\" event to be emitted when the\r\n          screen or 'cmdheight' area is cleared.\r\n\r\nFix #33844\r\nFix #34007",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Hope to resolve #33844 and #34007 here but there are some things yet unresolved:\r\n\r\n- Nvim's internal `msg_ext_visible` counter may prevent this event from emitting due to it getting out of sync after extui dismisses the hit-enter message. It's reset to 0 while our (or any) extui may still be showing messages (related #27963).\r\n- To resolve #34007 we would also have to emit this event (perhaps with another boolean indicating the source) when `msg_clr_eos_force()` is called, rather than just returning with `ext_messages` enabled.",
